#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. The Third Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 25. Akkodhasutta → akodho (avihiṃsā) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Akkodhasutta "
msgstr "25. Don’t Be Angry "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn11.25:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn11.25:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.25:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū … pe … bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.25:1.4"
msgid "“bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ deve tāvatiṃse anunayamāno tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, guiding the gods of the Thirty-Three, recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.515, sc2
msgctxt "sn11.25:2.1"
msgid "‘Mā vo kodho ajjhabhavi, "
msgstr "“Don’t let anger be your master, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:2.2"
msgid "mā ca kujjhittha kujjhataṃ; "
msgstr "don’t get angry at angry people. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:2.3"
msgid "Akkodho avihiṃsā ca, "
msgstr "Kindness and harmlessness "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ca paṭipadā → vasati sadā (bj, pts1) | vasatī sadā (s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn11.25:2.4"
msgid "ariyesu ca paṭipadā; "
msgstr "are always present in the noble ones. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:2.5"
msgid "Atha pāpajanaṃ kodho, "
msgstr "For anger crushes bad people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:2.6"
msgid "pabbatovābhimaddatī’”ti. "
msgstr "like a mountain.’” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn11.25:2.7"
msgid "Tatiyo vaggo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn11.25:3.1"
msgid "Chetvā dubbaṇṇiya māyā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:3.2"
msgid "accayena akodhano; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:3.3"
msgid "Desitaṃ buddhaseṭṭhena, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:3.4"
msgid "idañhi sakkapañcakanti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn11.25:3.5"
msgid "Sakkasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses with Sakka are complete. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn11.25:3.6"
msgid "Sagāthāvaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.516, sc4
msgctxt "sn11.25:4.1"
msgid "Devatā devaputto ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:4.2"
msgid "rājā māro ca bhikkhunī; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:4.3"
msgid "Brahmā brāhmaṇa vaṅgīso, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.25:4.4"
msgid "vanayakkhena vāsavoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "sn11.25:4.5"
msgid "Sagāthāvaggasaṃyuttapāḷi niṭṭhitā. "
msgstr "The Book With Verses is finished."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
